President Cyril Ramaphosa has lobbied big names for the much anticipated Investor Conference planned for October. He has invited China’s richest man, Jack Ma,to the October gathering. Ramaphosa is currently on an investment charm offensive trying  to raise R1,3 trillion in the next few years. The October conference is seen as a platform to help meet the target. He says having Jack Ma amongst the attendants will give impetus to what he wants to achieve. <a href="https://iono.fm/e/600209">Content hosted by iono.fm</a>  Watch below for more: 